Beavis and Butt-head Do America is a 1996 American animated comedy road film, based on the TV series Beavis and Butt-head. It was produced by Paramount Pictures in association with Geffen Pictures and MTV Films, and co-written and directed by creator Mike Judge. The film became the biggest December box-office opening in history until it was beaten the following year by Scream 2 and subsequently one week later by Titanic.
